    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9c587f46_15e40901",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/db/firestore/jobs.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 176,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-26T18:47:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We should think about this carefully. If we\u0027ve already inserted the job into the DB, returning an error doesn\u0027t seem correct, because then we\u0027ll try to insert the same jobs again. My general feeling is that if there is an error in ModifiedJobs/ModifiedTasks, the resolution of the error is to reset all subscribers and have GetModified* return an error for existing subscribers.\n\nI\u0027m not completely sure how to do this for push notifications (i.e. PubSub), but one possibility is to send heartbeats, where the receiver resets itself if it misses 2 heartbeats. Another possibility is to add a UUID to messages where the receiver resets itself if the UUID changes between messages.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 176,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 176,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "e7432b044c406b60b4c7e0b2a9131d0d82f1e000",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2b4b1924_eb9b4744",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/db/firestore/jobs.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 176,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-27T14:27:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can you explain a little more about the heartbeat idea?  Is the primary concern here that the scheduler might restart before it finishes sending messages?",
      "parentUuid": "9c587f46_15e40901",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 176,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 176,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "e7432b044c406b60b4c7e0b2a9131d0d82f1e000",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7852fda8_82652853",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/db/firestore/jobs.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 176,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-27T18:41:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Discussed in person.\n\nI think we could lose messages for a few reasons, like the process dying while there are messages in the queue or request timeouts sending messages to pubsub.\n\nThe idea of the heartbeat would be to send messages to all subscribers notifying them of which publishers they should expect to hear from (identified by a UUID). When a publisher detects an error that could cause the subscribers to miss messages, the publisher stops sending the heartbeat so that subscribers know there is something wrong (as opposed to no new modifications). The publisher could continue publishing with a new UUID.",
      "parentUuid": "2b4b1924_eb9b4744",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 176,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 176,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "e7432b044c406b60b4c7e0b2a9131d0d82f1e000",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
