    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1aaaa1c6_68465509",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/db/pubsub/modified.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 134,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-27T18:41:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think there are some things we know could be a problem, and it\u0027s not necessarily worth the time to make it bulletproof.\n\nThe in-memory impl. of GetModifiedTasks also guarantees that it\u0027s returning a consistent snapshot of tasks. There are ways we could ensure that with the pubsub impl., but right now we could get messages out of order or a partial set of updates for tasks modified in an atomic transaction.",
      "parentUuid": "2f406127_426d8160",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 134,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 134,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "e7432b044c406b60b4c7e0b2a9131d0d82f1e000",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5c7f97c8_641d1425",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/db/pubsub/modified.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 134,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-27T20:03:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Gotcha. I\u0027m not overly concerned about out-of-order messages, as long as the results returned by each call to GetModified returns sensible results, ie. some modified tasks may not show up until a later call, but if a given task was modified multiple times (and we received multiple messages for it), we return the latest version.  We can work around blamelist inconsistencies by processing tasks in chronological order by DbModified timestamp.",
      "parentUuid": "1aaaa1c6_68465509",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 134,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 134,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "e7432b044c406b60b4c7e0b2a9131d0d82f1e000",
